        void loginWithUsernamePassword(DeviceSecurityProfile deviceSecurityProfile)
                               throws PaydiantClientException
        The method implements the log in functionality using the username and password. In addition if the device is not registered to the user The device is registered up front prior to login.
        Parameters:
        deviceSecurityProfile - - instance of the deviceSecurityProfile object which encapsulates the device information and the user name password.
        Throws:
        PaydiantClientException - the paydiant client exception

      • loginByNonce

        void loginByNonce(DeviceSecurityProfile deviceSecurityProfile)
        Logs in the user using a nonce. If login requires MFA answer, then this method will need to be called again with the DeviceSecurityProfile instance returned from the IUserLoginExtendedListener.onPromptMFA(DeviceSecurityProfile) callback, with DeviceSecurityProfile.setQuestionAndAnswer(com.paydiant.android.core.domain.QuestionAndAnswer) properties set. Successful login will trigger the IUserLoginListener.onSuccess() and/or IUserLoginExtendedListener.onSuccess(java.util.Map) callback methods and any failures will be reported via IUserLoginListener.onError(com.paydiant.android.core.exception.PaydiantException) callback.
        Parameters:
        deviceSecurityProfile - - Initial call will require nonce and device properties populated. To provide MFA answers, use the returned DeviceSecurityProfile with questionAndAnswer properties populated.
        Since:
        5.3.0.2
        See Also:
        IUserLoginExtendedListener.onPromptMFA(DeviceSecurityProfile), ISecurityManagerFacade.loginByNonce(DeviceSecurityProfile)

      • loginByFederatedIdentity

        void loginByFederatedIdentity(DeviceSecurityProfile deviceSecurityProfile)
        Logs in the user using the information retrieved from identity service provider. If login requires MFA answer, then this method will need to be called again with the DeviceSecurityProfile instance returned from the IUserLoginExtendedListener.onPromptMFA(DeviceSecurityProfile) callback, with DeviceSecurityProfile.setQuestionAndAnswer(com.paydiant.android.core.domain.QuestionAndAnswer) properties set. Successful login will trigger the IUserLoginListener.onSuccess() and/or IUserLoginExtendedListener.onSuccess(java.util.Map) callback methods and any failures will be reported via IUserLoginListener.onError(com.paydiant.android.core.exception.PaydiantException) callback.
        Parameters:
        deviceSecurityProfile - - Initial call will require authorizationCode, identityProvider and device properties populated. To provide MFA answers, use the returned DeviceSecurityProfile with questionAndAnswer properties populated.
        Since:
        5.3.0.2
        See Also:
        IUserLoginExtendedListener.onPromptMFA(DeviceSecurityProfile), ISecurityManagerFacade.loginByFederatedIdentity(DeviceSecurityProfile)
